article.headline: ETSU 84, Stetson 49
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. (AP) -- Brad Nuckles scored 19 points and had 11 rebounds to lead East Tennessee State past cold-shooting Stetson 84-49 Thursday night and clinch the Atlantic Sun Conference regular-season title. East Tennessee (21-8, 15-2) bolted to a 27-7 lead with 7:20 left in the first half and it was never close thereafter. Stetson (11-18, 6-11 A-Sun) hit just 26.4 percent from the floor while the Bucs hit 55.2 percent. Nuckles was 6-of-7 from the floor and 3-of-3 from 3-point range in 30 minutes of play. Reserve Mike Smith added 14 points on 6-of-8 shooting and Courtney Pigram scored 12. Stetson had just one player in double figures, Garfield Blair with 11. He also had a team-high seven rebounds. East Tennessee gets the No. 1 seed in the conference tourney next week, which they are hosting.
